242
00:13:00,641 --> 00:13:01,508
WELL, I'LL BE!

243
00:13:01,508 --> 00:13:04,941
THIS IS EITHER
AN IDIOT OR A GENIUS!

244
00:13:04,941 --> 00:13:07,008
I LIKE THIS FELLOW!

245
00:13:07,008 --> 00:13:09,308
[LAUGHS]

246
00:13:09,308 --> 00:13:11,075
CHESS MASTER HEX.

247
00:13:11,075 --> 00:13:13,608
ESTIMATED TO BE 98 YEARS OLD.

248
00:13:13,608 --> 00:13:17,908
A PROGRAMMER THAT HAD BEEN
DUBBED A GENIUS FROM HIS TEENS.

249
00:13:17,908 --> 00:13:19,875
IN THE COSMO NET
CHESS TOURNAMENTS,

250
00:13:19,875 --> 00:13:22,908
HE HELD THE CHAMPION
SEAT FOR DECADES.

251
00:13:22,908 --> 00:13:25,841
HE APPLIED HIS INTELLECT TO
THE HYPERSPACE GATE PROJECT,

252
00:13:25,841 --> 00:13:28,075
JOINING THE PROGRAM
AT 30 YEARS OF AGE.

253
00:13:28,075 --> 00:13:30,775
HE EVENTUALLY DEVELOPED
THE CENTRAL CONTROL SYSTEM

254
00:13:30,775 --> 00:13:32,041
THAT ALL GATES USE TO THIS DAY.

255
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:35,741
BUT AFTER THAT,
HE STARTED TO HAVE DOUBTS.

256
00:13:35,741 --> 00:13:37,841
HE SAID THE DESIGN
HAD DEFECTS

257
00:13:37,841 --> 00:13:39,841
AND THE GATES
SHOULDN'T BE BUILT YET.

258
00:13:39,841 --> 00:13:41,308
HE WANTED TO RUN MORE TESTS.

259
00:13:41,308 --> 00:13:43,808
SO THEY FIRED HIM AND
BUILT THE GATES ANYWAY.

260
00:13:43,808 --> 00:13:45,375
HE'S BEEN MISSING
FOR THE LAST 50 YEARS.

261
00:13:45,375 --> 00:13:49,108
SO HE'S THE MASTERMIND
WHO TAUGHT THOSE BEGINNERS.

262
00:13:49,108 --> 00:13:50,341
BUT WHY?

263
00:13:50,341 --> 00:13:52,975
IS HE TRYING TO GET REVENGE
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS OR WHAT?

264
00:13:52,975 --> 00:13:56,875
MAYBE IF WE TRACK HIM DOWN,
WE CAN GET TO THE BOTTOM OF IT.

265
00:13:56,875 --> 00:13:57,775
HEY, ED?

266
00:13:57,775 --> 00:13:59,108
EDWARD IS VERY BUSY.

267
00:13:59,108 --> 00:14:00,141
TRY LATER.

268
00:14:00,141 --> 00:14:01,041
FORGET LATER.

269
00:14:01,041 --> 00:14:02,308
WE NEED SOME HELP NOW.

270
00:14:02,308 --> 00:14:04,275
GIVE ME THAT

271
00:14:04,275 --> 00:14:05,708
[HISSES]

272
00:14:05,708 --> 00:14:08,808
ED, WE'RE TRYING
TO FIND A GUY NAMED HEX.

273
00:14:08,808 --> 00:14:10,008
HE'S IN CYBERSPACE.

274
00:14:10,008 --> 00:14:13,008
HEX.
HEX THE CHESS MASTER.

275
00:14:13,008 --> 00:14:16,675
EDWARD IS PLAYING CHESS
AGAINST HIM RIGHT NOW.

276
00:14:16,675 --> 00:14:18,608
HUH?

277
00:14:29,875 --> 00:14:31,675
I TRACKED HIM
THROUGH EDWARD'S GAME,

278
00:14:31,675 --> 00:14:34,341
AND WE'RE COMING UP ON HIM.

279
00:14:34,341 --> 00:14:36,041
ARE YOU GUYS STANDING BY?

280
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:36,908
I DON'T LIKE THIS.

281
00:14:36,908 --> 00:14:38,908
HE MADE IT MUCH
TOO EASY TO TRACE HIM.

282
00:14:38,908 --> 00:14:40,375
THIS GUY'S TOO SMART FOR THAT.

283
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:41,708
MAYBE IT'S A FALSE TRAIL.

284
00:14:41,708 --> 00:14:42,875
I MEAN, LOOK WHERE
WE'RE HEADING.

285
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:44,875
WOULD HE BE IN A DUMP LIKE THAT?

286
00:14:44,875 --> 00:14:47,208
HOLD ON A MINUTE.

287
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:48,908
LISTEN TO ME.

288
00:14:48,908 --> 00:14:50,841
I HEARD ABOUT THIS PLACE
A LONG TIME AGO

289
00:14:50,841 --> 00:14:52,341
A KIND OF FLOATING SCRAP YARD

290
00:14:52,341 --> 00:14:54,875
WHERE THEY LEAVE
WRECKED GATE PARTS,

291
00:14:54,875 --> 00:14:56,941
ABANDONED SPACESHIPS,
AND SCRAP METAL.

292
00:14:56,941 --> 00:14:59,175
PEOPLE MOVED IN

293
00:14:59,175 --> 00:15:00,908
AND STARTED LIVING THERE
SQUATTERS AND DRIFTERS.

294
00:15:00,908 --> 00:15:04,008
WHY THE HELL WOULD THEY WANT
TO LIVE THERE OF ALL PLACES?

295
00:15:04,008 --> 00:15:04,875
THERE'S NO GOVERNMENT,

296
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:08,808
NO NATIONALITY,
NO TAXES, AND NO COPS.

297
00:15:08,808 --> 00:15:10,975
THEY SEE IT AS TOTAL FREEDOM.

298
00:15:10,975 --> 00:15:12,075
YEAH, RIGHT.

299
00:15:12,075 --> 00:15:15,341
IT WOULD ALSO MAKE IT
A PERFECT PLACE TO HIDE OUT.

300
00:15:28,875 --> 00:15:33,975
REMEMBER, THIS COULD BE A TRAP,
A CONTINUATION OF THE GAME.

301
00:15:33,975 --> 00:15:37,975
WHATEVER HAPPENS HAPPENS.

302
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:26,275
LOOKS LIKE
THERE'S AIR IN HERE.

303
00:16:26,275 --> 00:16:29,275
THEN THERE'S SOMEONE THERE.

304
00:16:29,275 --> 00:16:31,375
[BEEPING]

305
00:16:31,375 --> 00:16:32,675
HMM?

306
00:16:32,675 --> 00:16:34,175
HOW'S IT GOING, JET?

307
00:16:34,175 --> 00:16:36,975
JONATHAN, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING OUT HERE?

308
00:16:36,975 --> 00:16:38,675
TRACKING YOU, OF COURSE.

309
00:16:38,675 --> 00:16:39,875
THANKS FOR LEADING THE WAY.

310
00:16:39,875 --> 00:16:42,175
YOU MEAN YOU'VE
BEEN FOLLOWING US?

311
00:16:42,175 --> 00:16:43,041
WHAT FOR?

312
00:16:43,041 --> 00:16:44,241
IT'S LIKE THIS.

313
00:16:44,241 --> 00:16:47,808
I'VE GOT A SCORE TO SETTLE
WITH THE GUY YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.

314
00:16:53,841 --> 00:16:56,908
[SCREAMING]

315
00:16:56,908 --> 00:16:59,241
BYE-BYE.

316
00:17:08,008 --> 00:17:10,241
[LAUGHING]

317
00:17:23,008 --> 00:17:25,875
OOH!

318
00:17:25,875 --> 00:17:27,975
[CAT MEOWING]

319
00:17:31,241 --> 00:17:33,208
WHAT THE?

320
00:17:33,208 --> 00:17:38,808
[LAUGHING]

321
00:17:38,808 --> 00:17:40,075
[GASPS]

322
00:17:40,075 --> 00:17:41,875
WHAT'S THAT?

323
00:17:45,041 --> 00:17:46,241
UH, I

324
00:17:46,241 --> 00:17:48,041
[DOGS BARKING]

325
00:17:48,041 --> 00:17:52,041
WHAT THE HELL?

326
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:53,241
HUH?

327
00:17:53,241 --> 00:17:59,241
[SNORING]

328
00:17:59,241 --> 00:18:00,941
WHAT'S THIS?

329
00:18:00,941 --> 00:18:05,008
[LAUGHING]

330
00:18:05,008 --> 00:18:07,641
WHAT'S GOING ON?

331
00:18:07,641 --> 00:18:09,741
[LAUGHING]

332
00:18:21,975 --> 00:18:23,008
HI.

333
00:18:23,008 --> 00:18:26,708
PEACE TO THE WHOLE GALAXY
AND TO MY BANK ACCOUNT.

334
00:18:26,708 --> 00:18:27,808
LOVE, LOVE.

335
00:18:27,808 --> 00:18:30,275
DO YOU WANT ONE?

336
00:18:30,275 --> 00:18:33,275
AHH!

337
00:18:33,275 --> 00:18:34,941
WOW! WHOA!

338
00:18:34,941 --> 00:18:37,008
[LAUGHING]

339
00:18:45,341 --> 00:18:47,908
CHESS MASTER HEX,
I TAKE IT.

340
00:18:47,908 --> 00:18:48,975
DON'T TRY ANYTHING.

341
00:18:48,975 --> 00:18:50,075
UNDERSTAND?

342
00:18:50,075 --> 00:18:52,341
YOU BOTH, UH

343
00:18:52,341 --> 00:18:55,975
WELL, COULD YOU BE JUST
A LITTLE QUIETER, PLEASE?

344
00:18:55,975 --> 00:18:57,341
HUH?

345
00:18:57,341 --> 00:19:03,208
OLD MAN... HAND IT OVER!

346
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:04,275
HEY, HOLD ON A MINUTE.

347
00:19:04,275 --> 00:19:07,241
PRETENDING TO BE SENILE
WON'T GET YOU OUT OF THIS.

348
00:19:07,241 --> 00:19:08,141
WHO ARE YOU?

349
00:19:08,141 --> 00:19:09,108
EITHER YOU GIVE ME
THE MONEY YOU TOOK,

350
00:19:09,108 --> 00:19:12,208
OR I PUT A HOLE RIGHT
THROUGH YOUR BRAIN.

351
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:13,675
HEH HEH HEH!

352
00:19:13,675 --> 00:19:15,641
THAT'S QUITE
A LARGE PIPE THERE.

353
00:19:15,641 --> 00:19:18,075
HEY, WHAT YOU DOING, HEX?

354
00:19:18,075 --> 00:19:19,908
OH, YOU GOT TO SEE THIS!

355
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:22,208
MY FIRST FORMIDABLE
OPPONENT IN AGES!

356
00:19:22,208 --> 00:19:25,008
HE MUST BE SOME PLAYER
TO PIN YOU DOWN.

357
00:19:25,008 --> 00:19:26,008
WHAT'S YOUR NEXT MOVE?

358
00:19:26,008 --> 00:19:27,041
I DON'T KNOW.

359
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:28,008
LET'S HAVE LUNCH FIRST.

360
00:19:28,008 --> 00:19:30,941
YOU ATE LUNCH A FEW
MINUTES AGO, BLAST IT.

361
00:19:30,941 --> 00:19:32,641
REALLY? DID I LIKE IT?

362
00:19:32,641 --> 00:19:34,741
WHO ARE THESE GUYS?

363
00:19:34,741 --> 00:19:37,908
DON'T KNOW,
BUT THIS ONE'S LOSING IT.

364
00:19:37,908 --> 00:19:39,341
YOU LEAVE YOUR
BRAIN SOMEWHERE?

365
00:19:39,341 --> 00:19:42,741
YEAH, LIKE YOU CAN TALK,
YOU NUMBSKULL.

366
00:19:42,741 --> 00:19:46,975
ALL MY SAVINGS GONE.
I'LL NEVER GET IT BACK NOW.

367
00:19:46,975 --> 00:19:48,908
DAMN IT. GODDAMN IT!

368
00:19:48,908 --> 00:19:52,741
ANYONE, EVERYONE, YOU KNOW.

369
00:19:52,741 --> 00:19:54,741
IT'S ALL A MISTAKE!

370
00:19:54,741 --> 00:19:56,575
[SCREAMING]

371
00:19:58,975 --> 00:20:00,875
[LAUGHING]

372
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:10,008
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO WITH HIM?

373
00:20:10,008 --> 00:20:11,675
THE OLD DUFFER'S OUT OF TOUCH.

374
00:20:11,675 --> 00:20:15,308
HE CAN'T RECALL YESTERDAY,
LET ALONE 50 YEARS AGO.

375
00:20:15,308 --> 00:20:18,808
LUCKY FOR HIM,
HEX IS NO LONGER HERE.

376
00:20:18,808 --> 00:20:23,875
THERE'S NO ONE LEFT BUT AN OLD
MAN WHO LOVES TO PLAY GAMES.

377
00:20:27,603 --> 00:20:28,943
HEX WAS FURIOUS.

378
00:20:28,943 --> 00:20:31,104
HE WANTED REVENGE,
AND THIS IS HOW HE GOT IT.

379
00:20:31,104 --> 00:20:33,004
HE SET UP THE STING
TO KICK IN 50 YEARS LATER

380
00:20:33,004 --> 00:20:34,437
WHEN THE GATE WAS PRE-SCHEDULED

381
00:20:34,437 --> 00:20:37,471
FOR ITS FIRST
AUTOMATIC TECH UPGRADE.

382
00:20:37,471 --> 00:20:38,604
IT WAS ALL PLANNED OUT.

383
00:20:38,604 --> 00:20:41,771
HE EVEN ARRANGED FOR HIS
OPERATIVES TO CARRY CHESS PIECES

384
00:20:41,771 --> 00:20:45,071
TO LET YOU KNOW THAT HE HAD
FINALLY GOTTEN BACK AT YOU.

385
00:20:45,071 --> 00:20:48,904
BUT 50 YEARS IS A LONG TIME.

386
00:20:48,904 --> 00:20:50,004
HEX GOT OLD.

387
00:20:50,004 --> 00:20:50,904
THEN HE GOT SENILE.

388
00:20:50,904 --> 00:20:52,104
HE COMPLETELY FORGOT ABOUT

389
00:20:52,104 --> 00:20:56,104
THE TRAPS THAT
HE HIMSELF HAD SET.

390
00:20:56,104 --> 00:20:58,071
WELL, IT'S BETTER
FOR YOU THIS WAY.

391
00:20:58,071 --> 00:20:59,937
YOU KNOW HE WON'T
EXPOSE YOU NOW.

392
00:20:59,937 --> 00:21:02,404
YOUR DIRTY LITTLE SECRET
WILL REMAIN A SECRET.

393
00:21:02,404 --> 00:21:04,104
HE CAN'T TELL ANYONE

394
00:21:04,104 --> 00:21:06,404
ABOUT THE DEFECTS
YOU BUILT INTO THE GATES.

395
00:21:06,404 --> 00:21:07,737
SO THAT'S IT, THEN.

396
00:21:07,737 --> 00:21:09,237
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT IT.

397
00:21:09,237 --> 00:21:12,271
YOU JUST HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT US.

398
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:13,737
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

399
00:21:13,737 --> 00:21:15,104
MONEY? IS THAT IT?

400
00:21:15,104 --> 00:21:16,371
COME ON. SAY IT.

401
00:21:16,371 --> 00:21:21,337
WHAT'S YOUR PRICE TO KEEP FROM
LEAKING THIS THING TO THE PRESS?

402
00:21:21,337 --> 00:21:24,737
JUST LEAVE THE OLD GUY ALONE.

403
00:21:24,737 --> 00:21:26,104
CALL OFF THE BOUNTY HUNTERS.

404
00:21:26,104 --> 00:21:27,971
THAT'S ALL WE ASK.

405
00:21:27,971 --> 00:21:29,437
YOU SEE, ED WOULD BE UNHAPPY

406
00:21:29,437 --> 00:21:33,004
IF SHE LOST
HER FAVORITE CHESS PARTNER,

407
00:21:33,004 --> 00:21:37,771
AND WE WOULDN'T WANT THAT
TO HAPPEN, NOW, WOULD WE?

408
00:21:43,171 --> 00:21:45,271
ARE YOU PLAYING AGAIN?

409
00:21:45,271 --> 00:21:46,837
NOT AGAIN.

410
00:21:46,837 --> 00:21:47,904
ED'S STILL PLAYING.

411
00:21:47,904 --> 00:21:52,471
YOU MEAN YOU'VE PLAYED
THE SAME GAME FOR A WEEK?

412
00:21:52,471 --> 00:21:53,804
MMHMM.

413
00:21:53,804 --> 00:21:55,004
I SEE.

414
00:21:55,004 --> 00:21:57,971
WELL, GOOD LUCK, ED.

415
00:22:00,004 --> 00:22:02,871
YO, NEWBY, YOU'RE
IN A GOOD MOOD TODAY.

416
00:22:02,871 --> 00:22:04,137
HOWDY THERE, GUYS.

417
00:22:04,137 --> 00:22:06,104
HE'S AN EASYGOING
DUDE, AIN'T HE?

418
00:22:06,104 --> 00:22:07,737
SURE IS, ANTONIO.

419
00:22:07,737 --> 00:22:08,937
NICE FELLA.

420
00:22:08,937 --> 00:22:14,037
CHECKMATE.

421
00:22:14,037 --> 00:22:18,137
AAH!

422
00:22:18,137 --> 00:22:23,671
HE GOT ME!

423
00:22:30,071 --> 00:22:32,071
[CHIRPING]

424
00:22:44,871 --> 00:22:47,071
[SQUAWKING]

425
00:24:30,377 --> 00:24:32,956
LOVE IS TO BELIEVE
IN EVERYTHING.

426
00:24:32,956 --> 00:24:34,597
WAIT A MINUTE.
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

427
00:24:34,597 --> 00:24:36,564
LOVE IS THE HEART
THAT GIVES TO ALL.

428
00:24:36,564 --> 00:24:38,764
COME ON! THAT'S WHAT
THE STORY'S ABOUT!

429
00:24:38,764 --> 00:24:41,164
LOVE IS THE HEART
THAT ACCEPTS EVERYTHING.

430
00:24:41,164 --> 00:24:42,997
YOU KNOW I'M NOT BUYING THIS.

431
00:24:42,997 --> 00:24:44,764
WHITNEY,
YOU LOVE ME THAT MUCH.

432
00:24:44,764 --> 00:24:47,264
YOU REALLY CAN'T TRUST
THE PREVIEWS ON THIS SHOW.

433
00:24:47,264 --> 00:24:49,930
A ROMANTIC LOVE STORY
FOR ALL YOU LOVERS.

434
00:24:49,930 --> 00:24:52,997
NEXT EPISODE
MY FUNNY VALENTINE.

435
00:24:52,997 --> 00:24:54,164
IT'S GOTTA BE A LIE.

436
00:24:54,164 --> 00:24:56,197
YEAH.
SHE'S MAKING IT UP.

